"**I Didn 't Know My Own Strength**" is a song performed by American
[R&B](/wiki/R%26B "R&B")-[pop](/wiki/Pop_music "Pop music") singer [Whitney
Houston](/wiki/Whitney_Houston "Whitney Houston"), taken from her seventh
studio album _[I Look to You](/wiki/I_Look_to_You "I Look to You")_ (2009).

The song was written by Houston, award-winning writer, [Diane
Warren](/wiki/Diane_Warren "Diane Warren") and produced by [David
Foster](/wiki/David_Foster "David Foster"), both of whom have written and
produced for Houston before. The song was originally supposed to precede the
album's UK release on August 31, 2009 and U.S. release on September 1, 2009
but was cancelled in favor of "[I Look to You](/wiki/I_Look_to_You_\(song\) "I
Look to You \(song\)")" and "[Million Dollar Bill](/wiki/Million_Dollar_Bill
"Million Dollar Bill")".[1][2] However, the song was released on November 6,
2009 as a [promotional single](/wiki/Promotional_single "Promotional single").

A live performance was included in the 2014 CD/DVD release, _[Whitney Houston
Live: Her Greatest
Performances](/wiki/Whitney_Houston_Live:_Her_Greatest_Performances "Whitney
Houston Live: Her Greatest Performances")_.[3]

## Critical
reception[[edit](/w/index.php?title=I_Didn%27t_Know_My_Own_Strength_\(Whitney_Houston_song\)&action=edit&section=1
"Edit section: Critical reception")]

When reviewing the album _[Digital Spy](/wiki/Digital_Spy "Digital Spy")_
described the song along with the title track "the album's pair of classic
Whitney ballads."[4]

##
Background[[edit](/w/index.php?title=I_Didn%27t_Know_My_Own_Strength_\(Whitney_Houston_song\)&action=edit&section=2
"Edit section: Background")]

Though never officially released, UK columnist Lizzie Smith reported in the
_[Daily Mail](/wiki/Daily_Mail "Daily Mail")_ the song had been leaked to the
internet prior to its official release date.[5] However, music mogul [Clive
Davis](/wiki/Clive_Davis "Clive Davis") said at the album's official launch
party in [London](/wiki/London "London") that all of the tracks on the album
remain unfinished.[6][7][8][9] The song's release was originally confirmed by
Diane Warren who told _[Vibe Magazine](/wiki/Vibe_Magazine "Vibe Magazine")_
she had penned the single especially for Houston, and it would be released as
the first single.[10] At the album listening parties, Davis said the album
track "Call You Tonight" was a candidate for the lead single. Following
previous reports, this led to speculation that "I Didn't Know My Own Strength"
would receive a limited release to generate buzz for the album, whilst a
different song will be fully promoted and released to propel the album's
release. Title song "[I Look to You](/wiki/I_Look_to_You_\(song\) "I Look to
You \(song\)")" was released as the U.S. lead single whilst "[Million Dollar
Bill](/wiki/Million_Dollar_Bill "Million Dollar Bill")" (the second U.S.
release) became the international lead single. Houston performed the song on
[The Oprah Winfrey Show](/wiki/The_Oprah_Winfrey_Show "The Oprah Winfrey
Show") on September 15, 2009[11][12] and live on the 2009 American Music
Awards broadcast.
